(35, 0, 'Panjabi', 'panjabi', 'public/uploads/category/1737109680-untitled-design-(1).webp', 'Panjabi', '<h3><strong>Panjabi┬а</strong></h3><p>Panjabi is one of the most traditional outfits in Bangladesh, primarily worn by men on various religious, cultural, and social occasions. It is especially popular during Eid, Pohela Boishakh, weddings, Milad Mahfils, and other festive events.</p><p>In Bangladesh, Panjabis are usually made from cotton, silk, linen, and khadi fabrics. During summer, cotton and linen Panjabis are preferred for their lightweight and breathable nature, while khadi and silk Panjabis are more popular in winter. Traditional hand embroidery, block prints, and intricate designs add to the charm of Panjabis, making them even more attractive.</p><p>With changing fashion trends, Panjabi designs have evolved significantly. Modern styles such as short Panjabis, straight-cut Panjabis, and fusion designs have become particularly popular among the younger generation. From branded showrooms to local markets, the demand for Panjabis remains high across all segments.</p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p>As an essential part of BangladeshтАЩs cultural identity, Panjabi is more than just an outfitтАФit symbolizes tradition, heritage, and national pride.</p>', 0, 0, '2025-01-17 10:28:00', '2025-05-24 15:15:57'),
